User initiates the first roll of all 5 dice (random values between 1 and 6 inclusively). 
Display all 5 and allow the user to either score the roll or select which dice to keep and which reroll (if any). 
User initiates reroll if die were selected to reroll. Display all 5 dice and allow the user to score the roll or 
select which dice to keep and which to reroll (if any) one more time. 
	To score the roll, add all the values of the dice. 
	Show the score to the user and allow them to continue. If they choose to leave, display the totals for all their 
  rolls in the order they made them along with an indication of how many times they rerolled and how many dice they 
  rerolled in total (not counting the first roll).
